  description: "asyncio.wait function name and module identity checks in asynciowait172 namespace — asyncio.wait.__name__.__eq__('wait')==True (wait.__name__=='wait' (len=4: 'wait'=4); asyncio.wait(aws, *, timeout=None, return_when=ALL_COMPLETED) concurrently waits for a set of futures/tasks and returns two sets: done and pending; unlike asyncio.gather which returns results in order, wait returns sets and requires the caller to retrieve results from each future; asyncio.wait requires that aws be a non-empty iterable of awaitables; 'wait'=4 is the shortest function name among the five in this spec); asyncio.wait.__name__.__len__()==4 ('wait'=4: shortest in this spec — wait=4 < sleep=5 < gather=6 < create_task=11 < ensure_future=13); asyncio.wait.__module__.__eq__('asyncio.tasks')==True (wait.__module__=='asyncio.tasks' (len=13); all five asyncio task functions share this module); asyncio.wait.__module__.__len__()==13 ('asyncio.tasks'=13; KEY PATTERN: all five functions in this spec share __module__=='asyncio.tasks' (len=13) — this is the defining characteristic of asyncio.tasks functions vs asyncio event loop functions (__module__=='asyncio.events' or '_asyncio')); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: asynciowait172

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [wait_name_eq,  asyncio.wait.__name__.__eq__,    ["wait"],           true,  "wait.__name__ == 'wait' (len=4: shortest name in this spec; wait=4 < sleep=5 < gather=6); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [wait_name_len, asyncio.wait.__name__.__len__,   [],                 4,     "wait.__name__.__len__() == 4 ('wait'=4; shortest among five: wait=4 < sleep=5 < gather=6 < create_task=11 < ensure_future=13); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [wait_mod_eq,   asyncio.wait.__module__.__eq__,  ["asyncio.tasks"],  true,  "wait.__module__ == 'asyncio.tasks' (len=13; same as all five functions in this spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [wait_mod_len,  asyncio.wait.__module__.__len__, [],                 13,    "wait.__module__.__len__() == 13 ('asyncio.tasks'=13; all five task functions share this module path); verified with Python 3.14.3"]

